(Macronutrients are nutrients required in large quantities to provide energy and support) Tj
T*
(basic physiological functions.) Tj
T*
T*
(Carbohydrates Carbohydrates are the body's primary energy source, providing 4 kcal per) Tj
T*
(gram. They are classified as:) Tj
T*
T*
(- **Simple carbohydrates**: Monosaccharides \(glucose, fructose, galactose\) and) Tj
T*
(disaccharides \(sucrose, lactose, maltose\). Found in fruits, dairy, and processed sugars.) Tj
T*
T*
(- **Complex carbohydrates**: Polysaccharides including starch \(in grains, legumes,) Tj
T*
(potatoes\) and dietary fiber \(in vegetables, whole grains, legumes\).) Tj
T*
T*
(The glycemic index \(GI\) measures how quickly carbohydrates raise blood glucose. Low-GI) Tj
T*
(foods \(legumes, whole grains\) cause gradual rises, while high-GI foods \(white bread,) Tj
T*
(sugary drinks\) cause rapid spikes followed by crashes.) Tj
T*
T*
(Dietary fiber, while not digested for energy, is critical for:) Tj
T*
T*
(- Gut microbiome health) Tj
T*
T*
(- Blood sugar regulation) Tj
T*
T*
(- Cholesterol reduction) Tj
T*
T*
(- Bowel regularity and colon cancer prevention) Tj
T*
T*
